cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel method for improving the learning efficiency of reinforcement learning algorithms. It also involves the use of deep neural networks for approximating the state-action value function. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as reinforcement learning is a subfield of AI. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics) as reinforcement learning is commonly used in robotics for learning control policies. 

Since the proposed method involves the use of deep neural networks for approximating the state-action value function, it could also be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as deep learning is commonly used in computer vision tasks. 

Finally, it could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as reinforcement learning is used for control problems in various domains.
